      • getHeadersForType

        public static java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> getHeadersForType(java.lang.String mapKey)
        Returns the Collection of headers currently set for a defined resource/request type.

        There are predefined request resource/request headers that can be retrieved and even changed. The user is also able to retrieve custom header Collections previously stored using a custom mapKey.

        Ex:

        Parameters:
        mapKey -
        Returns:
        See Also:
        setHeadersForType(String,Collection), addHeaderForType(String, String), removeHeaderForType(String, String)

      • setHeadersForType

        public static void setHeadersForType(java.lang.String mapKey,
                     java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> headers)
        Wholesale set/replace the headers Collection to be used for a predefined or custom resource/request type. If the provided Collection is null then the headers mapped to the mapKey and the mapKey entry will be removed.
        Parameters:
        mapKey -
        headers -
        See Also:
        getHeadersForType(String), addHeaderForType(String, String), removeHeaderForType(String, String)
